   http://www.access.gpo.gov/su_docs/aces/aces150.html

   Congressional Research Service Reports
   http://www.senate.gov/~dpc/crs/
   The Congressional Research Service (CRS) is part of the legislative
   branch of the federal government. CRS, which is a department of the
   Library of Congress, works exclusively as a nonpartisan analytical,
   research, and reference arm for Congress. The CRS mission is to support
   an informed national legislature.

