   United States Code
   http://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode

   United States Government Manual is now available through GPO Access at
   http://www.access.gpo.gov/nara/nara001.html
   This reference source provides addresses, phone and fax numbers,
   and descriptions of duties for agencies of the executive, judicial, and
   leglislative branchs of the federal government. Also included are
   government corporations, commissions, committees, and independent
   establishments. Previous editions of the manual are also available on
   this site.

   U. S. Patents & Trademarks
   http://www.uspto.gov

   World Factbook
   This publication from the Central Intelligence agency is now
   available at http://www.odci.gov/cia/publications/factbook/index.html
   This reference source lists profiles of over 260 countries around the
   world. The profiles include a map, background information, and profiles
   of the people, government, economy, communications, transportation,
   military and transitional issues. The information is very current.
